H0.text: Hertz is the unit in which the frequency of a wave is measured.

H1.text: Meters are the units in which the frequency of a wave is measured.

H2.text: Hertz/second is the unit used to measure the frequency of a wave.

H3.text: Meters/minute are the units in which the frequency of a wave is measured.

A4.text: The hertz (symbol: Hz) is the unit of frequency in the International System of Units (SI), often described as being equivalent to one event (or cycle) per second.

A5.text: The hertz is an SI derived unit whose formal expression in terms of SI base units is 1/s or sâˆ’1, meaning that one hertz is one per second or the reciprocal of one second.
